    <item>
      <title>Operator Upgrade</title>
      <link>https://dell.github.io/csm-docs/docs/getting-started/upgrade/operator/driver_upgrade/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://dell.github.io/csm-docs/docs/getting-started/upgrade/operator/driver_upgrade/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h3 id=&#34;upgrading-drivers-with-dell-csm-operator&#34;&gt;&#xA;Upgrading Drivers with Dell CSM Operator &lt;a class=&#34;header-link&#34;  href=&#34;#upgrading-drivers-with-dell-csm-operator&#34; style=&#34; display: inline-block; opacity: 0; transition: opacity 0s ease-in-out; &#34; onmouseover=&#34;this.style.opacity=1;&#34; onmouseout=&#34;this.style.opacity=0;&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;svg fill=&#34;currentColor&#34; height=&#34;24&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; width=&#34;24&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;path d=&#34;M0 0h24v24H0z&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34;/&gt;&#xA;                &lt;path d=&#34;M3.9 12c0-1.71 1.39-3.1 3.1-3.1h4V7H7c-2.76 0-5 2.24-5 5s2.24 5 5 5h4v-1.9H7c-1.71 0-3.1-1.39-3.1-3.1zM8 13h8v-2H8v2zm9-6h-4v1.9h4c1.71 0 3.1 1.39 3.1 3.1s-1.39 3.1-3.1 3.1h-4V17h4c2.76 0 5-2.24 5-5s-2.24-5-5-5z&#34;/&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;You can update CSI Drivers installed by the Dell CSM Operator like any Kubernetes resource:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;/b&gt;Get the driver-object details using kubectl command:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;style&gt;&#xA;.visible-content {&#xA;  display: block;&#xA;}&#xA;.inline-content {&#xA;  display: inline;&#xA;}&#xA;&lt;/style&gt;&#xA;&lt;span id=&#34;&#34; class=&#34;visible-content 1&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;kubectl get csm -n powerstore&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;style&gt;&#xA;.visible-content {&#xA;  display: block;&#xA;}&#xA;.inline-content {&#xA;  display: inline;&#xA;}&#xA;&lt;/style&gt;&#xA;&lt;span id=&#34;&#34; class=&#34;visible-content 2&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;kubectl get csm -n isilon&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;style&gt;&#xA;.visible-content {&#xA;  display: block;&#xA;}&#xA;.inline-content {&#xA;  display: inline;&#xA;}&#xA;&lt;/style&gt;&#xA;&lt;span id=&#34;&#34; class=&#34;visible-content 3&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;kubectl get csm -n vxflexos&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;style&gt;&#xA;.visible-content {&#xA;  display: block;&#xA;}&#xA;.inline-content {&#xA;  display: inline;&#xA;}&#xA;&lt;/style&gt;&#xA;&lt;span id=&#34;&#34; class=&#34;visible-content 4&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;kubectl get csm -n powermax&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;style&gt;&#xA;.visible-content {&#xA;  display: block;&#xA;}&#xA;.inline-content {&#xA;  display: inline;&#xA;}&#xA;&lt;/style&gt;&#xA;&lt;span id=&#34;&#34; class=&#34;visible-content 5&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;kubectl get csm -n unity&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;style&gt;&#xA;.visible-content {&#xA;  display: block;&#xA;}&#xA;.inline-content {&#xA;  display: inline;&#xA;}&#xA;&lt;/style&gt;&#xA;&lt;span id=&#34;&#34; class=&#34;visible-content 4&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;p&gt;As of CSI PowerMax v2.14.0, the csi reverse proxy configuration and connectivity information has been migrated from a ConfigMap to a Secret. If the &lt;code&gt;powermax-creds&lt;/code&gt; secret format was not previously updated, reference &lt;strong&gt;Step 2&lt;/strong&gt; in &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../installation/kubernetes/powermax/csmoperator/#install-driver&#34;&gt;CSI Driver installation steps&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Operator Upgrade</title>
      <link>https://dell.github.io/csm-docs/docs/getting-started/upgrade/operator/upgrade/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://dell.github.io/csm-docs/docs/getting-started/upgrade/operator/upgrade/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Operator can be upgraded in 2 ways:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Using Operator Lifecycle Manager (OLM)&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Using script (for non-OLM based installation)&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;h4 id=&#34;using-olm&#34;&gt;&#xA;Using OLM &lt;a class=&#34;header-link&#34;  href=&#34;#using-olm&#34; style=&#34; display: inline-block; opacity: 0; transition: opacity 0s ease-in-out; &#34; onmouseover=&#34;this.style.opacity=1;&#34; onmouseout=&#34;this.style.opacity=0;&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;svg fill=&#34;currentColor&#34; height=&#34;24&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; width=&#34;24&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;path d=&#34;M0 0h24v24H0z&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34;/&gt;&#xA;                &lt;path d=&#34;M3.9 12c0-1.71 1.39-3.1 3.1-3.1h4V7H7c-2.76 0-5 2.24-5 5s2.24 5 5 5h4v-1.9H7c-1.71 0-3.1-1.39-3.1-3.1zM8 13h8v-2H8v2zm9-6h-4v1.9h4c1.71 0 3.1 1.39 3.1 3.1s-1.39 3.1-3.1 3.1h-4V17h4c2.76 0 5-2.24 5-5s-2.24-5-5-5z&#34;/&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;p&gt;The upgrade of the Operator is done via Operator Lifecycle Manager.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;Update approval&lt;/code&gt; (&lt;strong&gt;&lt;code&gt;InstallPlan&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; in OLM terms) strategy plays a role while upgrading dell-csm-operator on OpenShift. This option can be set during installation of dell-csm-operator on OpenShift via the console and can be either set to &lt;code&gt;Manual&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;Automatic&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Authorization v1.x</title>
      <link>https://dell.github.io/csm-docs/docs/getting-started/upgrade/operator/authorization_upgrade/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://dell.github.io/csm-docs/docs/getting-started/upgrade/operator/authorization_upgrade/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;upgrade-csm-authorization&#34;&gt;&#xA;Upgrade CSM Authorization &lt;a class=&#34;header-link&#34;  href=&#34;#upgrade-csm-authorization&#34; style=&#34; display: inline-block; opacity: 0; transition: opacity 0s ease-in-out; &#34; onmouseover=&#34;this.style.opacity=1;&#34; onmouseout=&#34;this.style.opacity=0;&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;svg fill=&#34;currentColor&#34; height=&#34;24&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; width=&#34;24&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;path d=&#34;M0 0h24v24H0z&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34;/&gt;&#xA;                &lt;path d=&#34;M3.9 12c0-1.71 1.39-3.1 3.1-3.1h4V7H7c-2.76 0-5 2.24-5 5s2.24 5 5 5h4v-1.9H7c-1.71 0-3.1-1.39-3.1-3.1zM8 13h8v-2H8v2zm9-6h-4v1.9h4c1.71 0 3.1 1.39 3.1 3.1s-1.39 3.1-3.1 3.1h-4V17h4c2.76 0 5-2.24 5-5s-2.24-5-5-5z&#34;/&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;This section outlines the upgrade steps for Container Storage Modules (CSM) for Authorization. The upgrade of CSM for Authorization is handled in 2 parts:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Upgrading the Authorization proxy server&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Upgrading CSI Driver, Authorization sidecar with Authorization module enabled&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;upgrading-the-authorization-proxy-server&#34;&gt;&#xA;Upgrading the Authorization Proxy Server &lt;a class=&#34;header-link&#34;  href=&#34;#upgrading-the-authorization-proxy-server&#34; style=&#34; display: inline-block; opacity: 0; transition: opacity 0s ease-in-out; &#34; onmouseover=&#34;this.style.opacity=1;&#34; onmouseout=&#34;this.style.opacity=0;&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;svg fill=&#34;currentColor&#34; height=&#34;24&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; width=&#34;24&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;path d=&#34;M0 0h24v24H0z&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34;/&gt;&#xA;                &lt;path d=&#34;M3.9 12c0-1.71 1.39-3.1 3.1-3.1h4V7H7c-2.76 0-5 2.24-5 5s2.24 5 5 5h4v-1.9H7c-1.71 0-3.1-1.39-3.1-3.1zM8 13h8v-2H8v2zm9-6h-4v1.9h4c1.71 0 3.1 1.39 3.1 3.1s-1.39 3.1-3.1 3.1h-4V17h4c2.76 0 5-2.24 5-5s-2.24-5-5-5z&#34;/&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Modifying the existing Authorization Proxy Server installation directly via &lt;code&gt;kubectl edit&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Observability</title>
      <link>https://dell.github.io/csm-docs/docs/getting-started/upgrade/operator/observability_upgrade/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://dell.github.io/csm-docs/docs/getting-started/upgrade/operator/observability_upgrade/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;upgrade-observability&#34;&gt;&#xA;Upgrade Observability &lt;a class=&#34;header-link&#34;  href=&#34;#upgrade-observability&#34; style=&#34; display: inline-block; opacity: 0; transition: opacity 0s ease-in-out; &#34; onmouseover=&#34;this.style.opacity=1;&#34; onmouseout=&#34;this.style.opacity=0;&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;svg fill=&#34;currentColor&#34; height=&#34;24&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; width=&#34;24&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;path d=&#34;M0 0h24v24H0z&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34;/&gt;&#xA;                &lt;path d=&#34;M3.9 12c0-1.71 1.39-3.1 3.1-3.1h4V7H7c-2.76 0-5 2.24-5 5s2.24 5 5 5h4v-1.9H7c-1.71 0-3.1-1.39-3.1-3.1zM8 13h8v-2H8v2zm9-6h-4v1.9h4c1.71 0 3.1 1.39 3.1 3.1s-1.39 3.1-3.1 3.1h-4V17h4c2.76 0 5-2.24 5-5s-2.24-5-5-5z&#34;/&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Observability module installed by the Dell CSM Operator can be updated like any Kubernetes resource.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Modifying the existing driver and module installation directly via &lt;code&gt;kubectl edit&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;kubectl get &amp;lt;driver-object&amp;gt; -n &amp;lt;driver-namespace&amp;gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;For example - If the CSI PowerScale driver is installed then run this command to get the object name&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
